hods, binary representation of numbers, using an editor and compiler from the command line, running programs with arguments from the command line, using libraries, and the use of basic data structures such as arrays, lists, sets, and maps. We will use Scala for this course.</li>\n<li>[Lectures] (<a href=\"http://otfried.org/courses/cs109/index.html\">http://otfried.org/courses/cs109/index.html</a>)</li>\n<li>[Assignments] (<a href=\"http://otfried.org/courses/cs109/index.html\">http://otfried.org/courses/cs109/index.html</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-21T07:52:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"viatsko/awesome-vscode","categoryHTML":"<h2>JavaScript</h2><h3>TypeScript</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eg2.tslint\">tslint</a> - TSLint for Visual Studio Code</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-21T07:14:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"xen0l/awesome-dtrace","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lists.freebsd.org/mailman/listinfo/freebsd-dtrace\">FreeBSD DTrace mailing list</a> - FreeBSD DTrace community mailing list.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-21T07:01:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DavidLambauer/awesome-magento2","categoryHTML":"<h2>Open Source Extensions</h2><h3>Adminhtml / Backend</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/SnowdogApps/magento2-menu\">Menu Editor</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/SnowdogApps/magento2-menu\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">185</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo